Arrays/Kadane_MaxSubarray.java

class Solution {
    public int maxSubArray(int[] nums) {
         int max_sum = nums[0];
         int n = nums.length;
          int curr_sum = 0;
         for(int i = 0 ; i< n; i++)
         {
           curr_sum += nums[i];
                if(curr_sum > max_sum)
                {
                    max_sum = curr_sum;
                }
                if(curr_sum < 0)
                {
                    curr_sum = 0;
                }
            }
         
         return max_sum;
    }
}
Approach (Kadane’s Algorithm)

Maintain a running sum (curr_sum)

If curr_sum becomes negative → reset to 0

Keep track of maximum sum found (max_sum)
